{"id":"DD4C31F6-8C7A-40FF-95CA-58EFF7E741E2","title":"Diet Coke Is Objectively Better","file":"/Users/me/Library/Mobile Documents/com~apple~CloudDocs/notes/roam/2026-04-06-13-52-37.diet-coke-is-objectively-better.org","point":1,"level":0,"tags":["essay","food","public","reflective"],"aliases":["Diet Coke essay","In Defense of Diet Coke"],"links_to":[],"linked_from":[],"ast":["org-data",{"pre-blank":0,"path":null,"ID":"DD4C31F6-8C7A-40FF-95CA-58EFF7E741E2","ROAM_ALIASES":"\"In Defense of Diet Coke\" \"Diet Coke essay\"","CREATED":"<2026-04-06 13:52>","LAST_MODIFIED":"<2026-04-06 13:52>","CATEGORY":null,"begin":1,"post-affiliated":1,"contents-begin":1,"contents-end":9804,"end":9804,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"org-data","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":184,"robust-end":9804,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":1,"post-affiliated":1,"contents-begin":1,"contents-end":268,"end":268,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"first-section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":1,"robust-end":268,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["property-drawer",{"begin":1,"post-affiliated":1,"contents-begin":14,"contents-end":179,"end":185,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"top-comment","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["node-property",{"key":"ID","value":"DD4C31F6-8C7A-40FF-95CA-58EFF7E741E2","begin":14,"post-affiliated":14,"contents-begin":null,"contents-end":null,"end":56,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"node-property","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null}],["node-property",{"key":"ROAM_ALIASES","value":"\"In Defense of Diet Coke\" \"Diet Coke essay\"","begin":56,"post-affiliated":56,"contents-begin":null,"contents-end":null,"end":115,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"node-property","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null}],["node-property",{"key":"CREATED","value":"<2026-04-06 13:52>","begin":115,"post-affiliated":115,"contents-begin":null,"contents-end":null,"end":144,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"node-property","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null}],["node-property",{"key":"LAST_MODIFIED","value":"<2026-04-06 13:52>","begin":144,"post-affiliated":144,"contents-begin":null,"contents-end":null,"end":179,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"node-property","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null}]],["keyword",{"key":"TITLE","value":"Diet Coke Is Objectively Better","begin":185,"post-affiliated":185,"contents-begin":null,"contents-end":null,"end":226,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null}],["keyword",{"key":"FILETAGS","value":"reflective public essay food","begin":226,"post-affiliated":226,"contents-begin":null,"contents-end":null,"end":268,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null}]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"Diet Coke Is Objectively Better","title":["Diet Coke Is Objectively Better"],"level":1,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":268,"post-affiliated":268,"contents-begin":303,"contents-end":9804,"end":9804,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":305,"robust-end":9802,"true-level":1,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":303,"post-affiliated":303,"contents-begin":303,"contents-end":944,"end":944,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":303,"robust-end":944,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":303,"post-affiliated":303,"contents-begin":303,"contents-end":661,"end":662,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Let me tell you something that will either make you nod along vigorously or close this tab in disgust: Diet Coke is better than regular Coke. Not \"better for you\" in the sad, self-denying sense that people mean when they grudgingly swap fries for a side salad. Better. Objectively. Empirically. In terms of the actual experience of drinking a cola beverage.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":662,"post-affiliated":662,"contents-begin":662,"contents-end":943,"end":944,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"I understand the eye-roll that just happened. Diet drinks occupy a strange cultural space -- associated with deprivation, with middle-aged women at Applebee's, with some joyless optimization of pleasure. The stigma is real and it is completely unearned. I am here to dismantle it.\n"]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"The Chemistry of the Thing","title":["The Chemistry of the Thing"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":944,"post-affiliated":944,"contents-begin":975,"contents-end":1912,"end":1912,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":977,"robust-end":1910,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":975,"post-affiliated":975,"contents-begin":975,"contents-end":1912,"end":1912,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":975,"robust-end":1912,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":975,"post-affiliated":975,"contents-begin":975,"contents-end":1400,"end":1401,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Regular Coke is sweetened with high-fructose corn syrup (or cane sugar in the glass bottle version, which its defenders will insist matters enormously). Either way, you're ingesting somewhere around 39 grams of sugar per 12-ounce can. That is a lot of sugar. Your taste receptors are not subtle instruments -- they detect sweetness and they report it loudly, and at that concentration, the sweetness becomes the whole story.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":1401,"post-affiliated":1401,"contents-begin":1401,"contents-end":1911,"end":1912,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Diet Coke uses aspartame, which has had an absolutely unhinged PR problem since the 1980s despite being one of the most studied food additives in history. Aspartame is roughly 200 times sweeter than sugar by weight, which means you need a vanishingly small amount of it -- small enough that it contributes essentially zero calories. More importantly for our purposes: it has a different ",["italic",{"begin":1788,"post-affiliated":null,"contents-begin":1789,"contents-end":1793,"end":1795,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"kind"],"of sweetness. It arrives quickly, it registers cleanly, and then it leaves. This is not a bug. This is the feature.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"The Finish","title":["The Finish"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":1912,"post-affiliated":1912,"contents-begin":1927,"contents-end":2821,"end":2821,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":1929,"robust-end":2819,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":1927,"post-affiliated":1927,"contents-begin":1927,"contents-end":2821,"end":2821,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":1927,"robust-end":2821,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":1927,"post-affiliated":1927,"contents-begin":1927,"contents-end":2365,"end":2366,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"The central flaw of regular Coke -- and I say this as someone who has drunk it, who understands its appeal, who is not some ascetic -- is that it lingers. After you swallow, the sweetness stays. It coats the back of your throat in a way that makes you simultaneously want more and also want it to stop. This is the HFCS signature: a cloying quality, a stickiness, a sense that your palate is now compromised for the next several minutes.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":2366,"post-affiliated":2366,"contents-begin":2366,"contents-end":2820,"end":2821,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Diet Coke finishes clean. The sweetness arrives, does its job, and then the carbonation takes over and scrubs the slate. What you're left with is that brief bright fizz and then -- nothing. Just the memory of having drunk something good. This is what all beverages should aspire to. This is what beer accomplishes with bitterness, what good espresso does with acidity. A clean finish is not an absence of flavor; it is a sign of compositional integrity.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"How the Carbonation Hits","title":["How the Carbonation Hits"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":2821,"post-affiliated":2821,"contents-begin":2850,"contents-end":3683,"end":3683,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":2852,"robust-end":3681,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":2850,"post-affiliated":2850,"contents-begin":2850,"contents-end":3683,"end":3683,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":2850,"robust-end":3683,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":2850,"post-affiliated":2850,"contents-begin":2850,"contents-end":3320,"end":3321,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"There is a real and noticeable difference in how the bubbles land. I cannot point to a controlled study on this specific phenomenon, but I have a theory, and my theory is that the sugar in regular Coke slightly dampens the sensation of carbonation -- the way fat coats the palate and mutes other flavors. Without that sugar load, Diet Coke's carbonation hits harder, sharper, more present. The fizz is the ",["italic",{"begin":3256,"post-affiliated":null,"contents-begin":3257,"contents-end":3262,"end":3264,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"point"],"of a cola drink, and in Diet Coke, you actually get it.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":3321,"post-affiliated":3321,"contents-begin":3321,"contents-end":3682,"end":3683,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"This is the cleanest argument for Diet Coke as the purer cola experience: strip away the thing that's masking the other flavors, and what you have is the actual taste of cola -- the phosphoric acid, the caramel, the vanilla, the mysterious proprietary blend that Coca-Cola has been cagey about since 1886 -- delivered with the full force of carbonation intact.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"The Stigma Is a Lie","title":["The Stigma Is a Lie"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":3683,"post-affiliated":3683,"contents-begin":3707,"contents-end":4526,"end":4526,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":3709,"robust-end":4524,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":3707,"post-affiliated":3707,"contents-begin":3707,"contents-end":4526,"end":4526,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":3707,"robust-end":4526,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":3707,"post-affiliated":3707,"contents-begin":3707,"contents-end":4044,"end":4045,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Somewhere along the way, diet drinks became coded as a form of self-punishment. You order a Diet Coke and someone at the table raises an eyebrow. You bring a twelve-pack to a party and someone makes a comment. The implicit message is that you are either on a diet (embarrassing) or afraid of sugar (joyless) or some combination of both.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":4045,"post-affiliated":4045,"contents-begin":4045,"contents-end":4525,"end":4526,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"This cultural baggage is bizarre when you examine it. Nobody mocks someone for preferring dry wine over sweet wine. Nobody suggests that choosing black coffee over a caramel macchiato is sad and restrictive. We readily accept that palates can prefer less sweetness without that preference being pathological. The diet drink stigma is just snobbery wearing the costume of hedonism -- the insistence that ",["italic",{"begin":4448,"post-affiliated":null,"contents-begin":4449,"contents-end":4453,"end":4455,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"more"],"sugar equals ",["italic",{"begin":4468,"post-affiliated":null,"contents-begin":4469,"contents-end":4473,"end":4475,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"more"],"enjoyment, which is not how taste actually works.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"The Converts","title":["The Converts"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":4526,"post-affiliated":4526,"contents-begin":4543,"contents-end":5694,"end":5694,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":4545,"robust-end":5692,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":4543,"post-affiliated":4543,"contents-begin":4543,"contents-end":5694,"end":5694,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":4543,"robust-end":5694,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":4543,"post-affiliated":4543,"contents-begin":4543,"contents-end":4971,"end":4972,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"There is a specific subset of humans who switched to Diet Coke at some point -- maybe for health reasons, maybe out of curiosity, maybe because it was the only thing in the fridge -- and who now cannot go back. I am one of these people. We are not suffering. We did not develop a tolerance for something inferior out of necessity. What happened is that our palates recalibrated, and now regular Coke tastes like drinking syrup.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":4972,"post-affiliated":4972,"contents-begin":4972,"contents-end":5445,"end":5446,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"The conversion experience is remarkably consistent across people who go through it. For about two weeks, Diet Coke tastes wrong -- too thin, too artificial, somehow both sweet and not sweet enough. Then something shifts. The sugar in regular Coke starts to taste excessive. The finish starts to feel cloying. And then one day you take a sip of regular Coke and you genuinely cannot understand why you ever preferred it. The scales fall from your eyes. The convert is born.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":5446,"post-affiliated":5446,"contents-begin":5446,"contents-end":5693,"end":5694,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"This is not conditioning yourself to accept less. It is recalibrating away from sugar-saturation toward something more nuanced. The same thing happens when people cut back on salt and start tasting food differently. It is not loss. It is clarity.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"Temperature","title":["Temperature"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":5694,"post-affiliated":5694,"contents-begin":5710,"contents-end":6797,"end":6797,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":5712,"robust-end":6795,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":5710,"post-affiliated":5710,"contents-begin":5710,"contents-end":6797,"end":6797,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":5710,"robust-end":6797,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":5710,"post-affiliated":5710,"contents-begin":5710,"contents-end":6039,"end":6040,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Both Cokes are temperature-sensitive, but Diet Coke is less forgiving on the warm end and more rewarding on the cold end. A warm Diet Coke is genuinely unpleasant -- the aspartame sweetness becomes more prominent, the carbonation dies, and you are left with something that tastes vaguely medicinal. I will not pretend otherwise.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":6040,"post-affiliated":6040,"contents-begin":6040,"contents-end":6546,"end":6547,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"But a properly cold Diet Coke -- properly cold meaning just above freezing, the kind you get from a refrigerator that is maybe set a bit too cold, ideally with a few ice crystals forming if you've left it in the freezer for fifteen minutes -- is one of the more perfect sensory experiences available to a person. The cold suppresses the sweetness slightly, the carbonation is at its most aggressive, and the whole thing lands with an immediacy that is genuinely hard to describe without sounding unhinged.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":6547,"post-affiliated":6547,"contents-begin":6547,"contents-end":6796,"end":6797,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Temperature matters more to Diet Coke than to regular Coke because Diet Coke has less going on to mask its flaws. This is actually an argument in its favor: it is an honest beverage. It does not hide behind sugar. Treat it right and it rewards you.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"Can vs. Bottle vs. Fountain","title":["Can vs. Bottle vs. Fountain"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":6797,"post-affiliated":6797,"contents-begin":6829,"contents-end":8137,"end":8137,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":6831,"robust-end":8135,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":6829,"post-affiliated":6829,"contents-begin":6829,"contents-end":8137,"end":8137,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":6829,"robust-end":8137,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":6829,"post-affiliated":6829,"contents-begin":6829,"contents-end":6934,"end":6935,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"This is where Diet Coke splits into genuinely distinct experiences, and I have opinions about all three.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":6935,"post-affiliated":6935,"contents-begin":6935,"contents-end":7302,"end":7303,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"The aluminum can is the canonical Diet Coke experience and the correct one. The metal imparts nothing, the carbonation is preserved perfectly, and the can itself is cold in your hand in a satisfying way. The ratio of opening-to-drinking is also exactly right -- the smaller aperture means you're getting a more concentrated stream of cold liquid. The can is correct.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":7303,"post-affiliated":7303,"contents-begin":7303,"contents-end":7616,"end":7617,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"The plastic bottle is worse. The carbonation degrades faster, the plastic interacts with the flavor in ways I cannot precisely describe but can reliably detect, and it warms up too quickly. A Diet Coke from a plastic bottle is a Diet Coke compromised. It is acceptable in conditions where the can is unavailable.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":7617,"post-affiliated":7617,"contents-begin":7617,"contents-end":8136,"end":8137,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Fountain Diet Coke is its own thing entirely -- chaotic neutral. McDonald's fountain Diet Coke is famously, documentably excellent, allegedly because they pre-chill their syrup and use a higher syrup-to-water ratio and filter their water more aggressively. A fountain Diet Coke from McDonald's is arguably the best single Diet Coke you can obtain. A fountain Diet Coke from a gas station dispenser that hasn't been serviced recently is the worst. The variance is enormous. The can has no variance. The can is reliable.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"The Pure Cola Experience","title":["The Pure Cola Experience"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":8137,"post-affiliated":8137,"contents-begin":8166,"contents-end":9044,"end":9044,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":8168,"robust-end":9042,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":8166,"post-affiliated":8166,"contents-begin":8166,"contents-end":9044,"end":9044,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":8166,"robust-end":9044,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":8166,"post-affiliated":8166,"contents-begin":8166,"contents-end":8635,"end":8636,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Here is the thing that Diet Coke's detractors consistently miss: sugar, at the concentrations present in regular Coke, is not just an ingredient. It is a masking agent. It saturates your sweetness receptors so thoroughly that you cannot fully taste the other things in the beverage -- the phosphoric acid brightness, the caramel depth, the citrus oils, the vanilla, the spices. Regular Coke is a flavor system in which all the interesting parts are buried under sugar.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":8636,"post-affiliated":8636,"contents-begin":8636,"contents-end":8939,"end":8940,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Diet Coke is what happens when you remove the masking agent. The aspartame provides sweetness -- enough to make it a sweet drink -- but it does not dominate. The other flavors have room. You can actually taste the cola. It is, in a genuine sense, the purer expression of what Coca-Cola is trying to be.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":8940,"post-affiliated":8940,"contents-begin":8940,"contents-end":9043,"end":9044,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"I am aware this argument infuriates regular Coke drinkers. I am making it anyway because I believe it.\n"]]],["headline",{"pre-blank":1,"raw-value":"Try It Cold From a Can","title":["Try It Cold From a Can"],"level":2,"priority":null,"tags":null,"todo-keyword":null,"todo-type":null,"footnote-section-p":null,"archivedp":null,"commentedp":null,"begin":9044,"post-affiliated":9044,"contents-begin":9071,"contents-end":9804,"end":9804,"post-blank":0,"secondary":{"title":null},"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":9073,"robust-end":9802,"true-level":2,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["section",{"begin":9071,"post-affiliated":9071,"contents-begin":9071,"contents-end":9804,"end":9804,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":"section","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":9071,"robust-end":9804,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},["paragraph",{"begin":9071,"post-affiliated":9071,"contents-begin":9071,"contents-end":9463,"end":9464,"post-blank":1,"secondary":null,"mode":"planning","granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"Here is what I am asking of you, if you are a skeptic: buy a twelve-pack. Put it in your coldest refrigerator. Wait until the cans are genuinely, properly cold -- not just chilled, but cold. Then open one, do not pour it over ice, drink it directly from the can, and pay attention to what's happening. Notice the finish. Notice the carbonation. Notice that you can taste the cola underneath.\n"],["paragraph",{"begin":9464,"post-affiliated":9464,"contents-begin":9464,"contents-end":9804,"end":9804,"post-blank":0,"secondary":null,"mode":null,"granularity":null,"cached":null,"org-element--cache-sync-key":null,"robust-begin":null,"robust-end":null,"true-level":null,"buffer":null,"deferred":null,"structure":null,"parent":null},"You might not convert. Some people don't, and I accept that preferences are real. But I would bet that the experience is different from what you expect, and that the version of Diet Coke you have in your head -- thin, sad, vaguely chemical -- does not match what you actually find in that cold aluminum can. Give it the chance it deserves.\n"]]]]]}